Describe an activity you usually do that wastes your time
- what it is
- when you usually do it
- why you do it
- explain why you think it wastes your time

I'd like to talk about browsing social media on my phone, which is an activity I tend to spend far too much time on. Although I don't track it precisely, I would say I spend around three or four hours a day scrolling through different platforms.
I usually do this in my free time, especially after work or before going to bed. Initially, I use social media to check updates, stay informed about current events, and keep in touch with friends and family. However, more often than not, I end up endlessly scrolling through new newsfeed without really paying attention to anything.
I think the main reason I keep doing it is because it helps me relax and temporarily escape from stress. Watching short videos or reading random posts can be quite entertaining. That said, I have to admit that I've become somewhat dependent on it, as I often find myself reaching for my phone even when I should be focusing on something more important.
I consider this a waste of time for several reasons. Firstly, it distracts me from completing important tasks and reduces my overall productivity. Secondly, although it provides short-term entertainment, it doesn't offer much long-term value. I have tried to cut down on my usage by deleting some apps, but unfortunately, I tend to fall back into the same habit after a short time.
Overall, while social media can be useful in moderation, I believe I spend far too much time on it, and I need to manage it more effectively in the future.
